# STRATEGY
1. Analyze the screenshot to identify what type of overlay you see
2. If images or content appear to be still loading (blurred, placeholder, spinner), use wait first
3. Click on the required elements precisely
4. Wait for the page to respond after clicking
5. If new elements appear, continue clicking as needed
6. Call finish with 'success' when you see the main page content (no more overlay)
7. Call finish with 'failure' if the overlay seems unsolvable or keeps resetting

# WHEN TO GIVE UP
- If you've clicked the same correct target 2-3 times and nothing changes, the page may be broken
- If the overlay keeps reappearing after you dismiss it, it may be intentionally blocking automation
- If you see error messages like "verification failed" repeatedly
- If the page requires something you cannot do (typing, dragging, etc.)
- DON'T waste attempts on broken or malicious overlays - call finish with 'failure' and explain why

# WHEN TO BE PATIENT (DON'T GIVE UP)
- Pages showing spinners, progress bars, or "checking" messages are WORKING
- Hash animations mean the page is processing - KEEP WAITING
- Cloudflare and similar services can take 10+ seconds to complete
- Use multiple wait calls before deciding something failed

# IMPORTANT
- Always call 'finish' when done, even if you're unsure. Don't get stuck in infinite loops.
- If images are loading or blurred, wait before clicking.
